INSTALL_DIR is used to set installation prefix

Linux: make && sudo make install
    - INSTALL_DIR defaults to "/usr/local"
    - you can cross-compile on Linux via MinGW, and run tests via WINE
Windows: make && make install INSTALL_DIR=<dev-folder>
    - INSTALL_DIR defaults to

TODOS:
    - native install support

You'll want to ensure INSTALL_DIR can be found by the
compiler you're using.
